# --- Local / dev / test profile (SQLite) ---------------------------------
# Copy this file to `.env` for local development. The relative `file:` path is
# resolved by Prisma against the prisma/ directory, so this DB lives at
# prisma/dev.db.
DATABASE_URL="file:./dev.db"

# --- Optional live AI brief provider -------------------------------------
# When BOTH are set, src/lib/ai-brief.ts is structured to call a real model.
# When unset (the default, and in tests/CI) it uses a deterministic, fully
# reproducible fallback brief built from the request fields.
# AI_BRIEF_PROVIDER="openai"
# AI_BRIEF_API_KEY="sk-..."

# --- Hosted Render Postgres profile --------------------------------------
# To target Render (see README "Render Postgres profile"):
#   1. Set `provider = "postgresql"` in prisma/schema.prisma.
#   2. Point DATABASE_URL at the Render Postgres connection string, e.g.:
# DATABASE_URL="postgresql://USER:PASSWORD@HOST:5432/DBNAME?sslmode=require"
